\begin_layout Standard
The NaiveThroughTime() function allows the user to easily compute rolling
 (fixed window length) or recursive (expanding window length) forecasts
 for a specific naive forecast type.
 The following sample script computes the 1- to 4-steps ahead seasonal mean
 (
\family typewriter
smeanf
\family default
) forecasts over time.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Doublebox
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
thickness "0.4pt"
separation "3pt"
shadowsize "4pt"
framecolor "black"
backgroundcolor "none"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset listings
lstparams "basicstyle={\footnotesize\ttfamily}"
inline false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

bundle b = null      # generate an empty bundle
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

b.y = x              # put objetcs into the bundle
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

b.h = 4              # max.
 horizon
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

b.wsize = 33         # window size
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

string which = "smeanf"   # choose a method
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

NaiveThroughTime(&b, which) # Call the function
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

matrix FC = b.FC     # grab matrix of forecasts
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

print FC             # rows: period being forecasted, cols: fc-horizon
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The results are stored in matrix 
\family typewriter
FC
\family default
.
 Thus, the 1-step ahead forecast for series 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

 made in 1980Q1 for 1980Q2 is 1.0059.
\end_layout

