backgroundcolor "none"
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\family typewriter
GnuPlotFun(bundle &b)
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Return type: 
\family typewriter
void
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The function argument is a single bundle element which must include some
 basic information.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
The 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

standard
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 plotting option
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The most basic type of plotting option is the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

standard
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 option.
 This option covers various styles such as (i) lines, (ii) linesplots, (iii)
 impulses, (iv) vertical bars and (v) horizontally shaded areas.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to plot numerical values in a specific style, the user has to pass
 specifically named matrices to 
\family typewriter
GPlotFun()
\family default
 as shown in Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab:Overview-style-options"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 This is a flexible framework which could be easily extended in future.
\begin_inset Note Note
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
vlines, hfilled and vfilled could also have the LHS-option.
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

